            "sections": [
              {
                "heading": "Overview",
                "text": "Transaction: all operations succeed or all rollback. ACID properties.\nconn.setAutoCommit(false) -> operations -> conn.commit() on success or conn.rollback() on exception.\nConnection pooling (HikariCP): reuse existing connections instead of creating new ones each request. Much faster."
              },
              {
                "heading": "Code Example",
                "code": "conn.setAutoCommit(false);\ntry {\n    PreparedStatement debit = conn.prepareStatement(\n        \"UPDATE accounts SET balance=balance-? WHERE id=?\");\n    debit.setDouble(1,5000); debit.setInt(2,1); debit.executeUpdate();\n\n    PreparedStatement credit = conn.prepareStatement(\n        \"UPDATE accounts SET balance=balance+? WHERE id=?\");\n    credit.setDouble(1,5000); credit.setInt(2,2); credit.executeUpdate();\n\n    conn.commit();  // success!\n    System.out.println(\"Transfer successful!\");\n} catch (SQLException e) {\n    conn.rollback();  // undo everything!\n    System.err.println(\"Failed, rolled back: \"+e.getMessage());\n} finally {\n    conn.setAutoCommit(true);\n}"
              }
            ],
